{"type":"message","id":"5d1bcbd5","parentId":"a4c4cdae","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:42:14.370Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9lkgsceg2zbj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\nCAUSAL-COMPOSITIONAL-INTERFACE.md\r\nCFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\nCFI_RESULTS.md\r\nCFI-CONCEPT-LEVEL-BREAKTHROUGH.md\r\nCOMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\r\nCOMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\r\nCOMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md\r\nGAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\nTEMPORALATTENTION-INTEGRATION-SPEC.md\r\nTIC_RESULTS.md\r\nTIC-CRITIQUE.md\r\nTIC-EXPERIMENT.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":634,"aggregated":"ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\nCAUSAL-COMPOSITIONAL-INTERFACE.md\r\nCFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\nCFI_RESULTS.md\r\nCFI-CONCEPT-LEVEL-BREAKTHROUGH.md\r\nCOMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\r\nCOMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\r\nCOMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md\r\nGAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\nTEMPORALATTENTION-INTEGRATION-SPEC.md\r\nTIC_RESULTS.md\r\nTIC-CRITIQUE.md\r\nTIC-EXPERIMENT.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774377734369}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a63af8b","parentId":"5d1bcbd5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:42:32.589Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the hybrid scoring experiment. I'll implement it as an experiment script.","thinkingSignature":"38d55182aeec08b526b9c1072578166d412ee69de638e5c058a92ad997946ada"},{"type":"text","text":"Creating the experiment implementation:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xzh0hncxq2eq_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md","content":"# Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\n**Status:** RUNNING\n\n## Experiment Design\n\n### Hypothesis\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 BUT capped at freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33 → min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 → score = 1.0\n- Favor research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → moderate score based on both dimensions\n- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" from \"Phase 1\" based on frequency normalization\n\n### Formula Implementation\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * freq_normalized\n```\n\n### Token Scoring Examples\n| Token | CFI | Freq | freq/120 | Hybrid Score | Classification |\n|-------|-----|------|----------|--------------|----------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.33→1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 1.13→1.0 | 0.96 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"research\" | 0.75 | 80 | 0.67 | 0.50 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"architecture\" | 0.60 | 40 | 0.33 | 0.20 | Trajectory (allow) |\n\n### Key Insight\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps the frequency contribution, so even freq=160 tokens score at most 1.0 on the frequency axis, but they still get the CFI bonus. Wait—that's not right for penalizing constants.\n\n### Revised Formula Logic\nActually, we want HIGH scores for research trajectory tokens and LOW scores for constants. Let's reconsider:\n\nIf freq(T) = 160 (constants):\n- min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\n- CFI(constants) ≈ 1.0\n- score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (HIGH)\n\nIf freq(T) = 40 (research tokens):\n- min(1, 40/120) = 0.33\n- CFI(research) ≈ 0.60\n- score = 0.60 × 0.33 = 0.20 (LOW)\n\nThis is BACKWARDS. High scores go to constants.\n\n### Corrected Formula for Penalizing Constants\nWe want constants to score LOW:\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_penalty = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_penalty)  # Low freq → high score, High freq → low score\n```\n\nNow:\n- freq=160: score = 1.0 × (1 - 1.0) = 0.0 (PENALIZED)\n- freq=40: score = 0.6 × (1 - 0.33) = 0.6 × 0.67 = 0.40 (REWARDED)\n\n### Final Formula\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    \"\"\"\n    score(T) = CFI(T) × (1 - min(1, freq(T)/120))\n    \n    High CFI + Low freq = HIGH score (research trajectory)\n    High CFI + High freq = LOW score (constant format)\n    \"\"\"\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_normalized)\n```\n\n## Experiment Results (TBD)\nWill run on 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:42:02\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2305,"output":1031,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15581,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774377734371}}
